      "content": "\u003cdiv class\u003d\"introduction img-head\"\u003e\r\n  \u003cdiv class\u003d\"header\"\u003e\r\n    \u003cimg src\u003d\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,\u003d\" alt\u003d\"\" \r\n        alt\u003d\"App Icon\"\u003e\r\n    \u003ch3\u003ePrice Elasticity Analytical App\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n  \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\r\n  \u003csection\u003e\r\n    \u003ch4\u003eOverview\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n      The Price Elasticity Analytical App measures how sensitive the quantity demanded of a good or service is to changes in its price. It quantifies the percentage change in quantity demanded resulting from a 1% change in price. This understanding is crucial for businesses to make data-driven decisions regarding pricing strategies, revenue optimization, and demand forecasting.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n  \u003c/section\u003e\r\n\r\n  \u003csection\u003e\r\n    \u003ch4\u003eInput\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n    \u003cul\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Business Level Selection: Users choose the analysis level (Country, Distributor, or Retailer).\u003c/li\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Analysis Triggers: Users initiate data exploration or main analysis by clicking dedicated buttons.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n  \u003c/section\u003e\r\n\r\n  \u003csection\u003e\r\n    \u003ch4\u003eOutput\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n    \u003cul\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Sales and Trend Visualizations: Charts display total sales over time, long-term trends, and seasonal patterns.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Price Elasticity Estimates: Estimates for SKUs at country, region, or store levels.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Optimal Pricing Insights: Charts illustrate total revenue over price (revenue parabola) and total revenue over volume.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Elasticity Breakdowns: Lists of retailers and regions with price elasticity, highlighting those with negative (sensitive) or positive (rare, luxury) elasticity.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n  \u003c/section\u003e\r\n\r\n  \u003csection\u003e\r\n    \u003ch4\u003eBenefits\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n    \u003cul\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Optimal Pricing Strategy: Helps businesses set optimal prices by understanding demand sensitivity.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Revenue Optimization: Identifies price points that maximize revenue.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Accurate Demand Forecasting: Aids in forecasting demand changes in response to price shifts, crucial for inventory and production.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Effective Promotion Planning: Allows businesses to evaluate and optimize promotional campaigns.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Informed Product Planning: Guides decisions for new product pricing and market positioning.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n  \u003c/section\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n",
